The paper deals with image enhancement using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the optimization of parameters using back-propagation, which is a key aspect of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses Retinex theory, which is a well-known image processing technique and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves the use of multi-scale processing, which is a common technique in multimedia processing (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with image processing and enhancement, which is a sub-topic of graphics (cs.GR).
